cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.LG 

The paper deals with the automatic segmentation of high-resolution 3D surface reconstructions of petroglyphs, which involves computer vision, graphics, and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with the cultural heritage domain, which falls under cs.GR (Graphics). The use of 3D scanning hardware and reconstruction algorithms involves multimedia processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also uses machine learning algorithms, which fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
